annotation.TEXT: Also, the coins stop draining while you're in this room, giving you a breather. Now, I hope you've banked several coins by now, because the game only gives you 3 more here. (15 should be plenty, but if you have less than about 7, that could be trouble.)
Ha! You're not burning me this time!

Okay, I made it to midpoint. Now, remember how I said that the game throws you a little bone if you blow it in the second half? Well, let me just Start+Select out and reenter from the midpoint entrance...
Ooh, the next level will be Ninth Cave! However, I'm not doing it today. Now, let me just speed through the first half of Fiery Coin Rush! again...
Yeah, those lower coins are definitely trickier. I'm going to challenge myself to get them all, even though they're pretty much pointless.

Yep, it coinifies (is that even a word?) the undead duders. Oddly enough, while it'll also transform any currently present Bullet Bills into coins, it won't have any effect on newly fired bullets after being activated.

I think these are one of the most annoying custom sprites out there. Why were they made to be like this, instead of behaving more like the flashing Missile Bills from SMB3, which travel at the same speed as normal Bullet Bills and don't move vertically, only changing direction horizontally?
This is not exactly the time to be Chuck tap dancing...
Argh... This is not the time to be forced to wait for enemy fireballs! (This is also not the time to check every pipe either!)

However, it's still not going to be a walk in the park, as the jumps are still tricky, and 7 coins isn't very much to start with, so you've gotta pick up just about every coin as you progress in order to not run out.
Geez! Good luck with this place if you don't have a cape!
Glitch!
Huh. The game shrunk me, but didn't kill me, when my coins hit zero while I was in the pipe. (I noticed earlier that my coins kept counting down while I was going through a pipe.)
Nuts. Just 30. Also, my bonus feather has gotten stuck in the ceiling, but that's okay, since I knew it would get stuck up there, and I wanted to keep my flower anyway.
Really, game?! Ugh... (Maybe I could've checked to see if that previous flower was still there, but time is tight enough as it is.)
Hmm... Looks like a puzzle. Sniff, sniff... Smells like a puzzle, too. However... (*Lick*) It tastes like chicken!
BGM: Super Mario Bros. - Metal Version
Ah, and here we are in world 6, after having passed through the Final World Gateway.
BGM: CUSTOM - Bossin' Me Around by Spigmike
Yay!
Oh, man. Bullet generator. Oh, man. Silver P-switch. Oh, man. Suicidal Bob-omb Bro.
Now, starting from here, the game reinitializes your coins, and then hands you 7, which I think is the bare minimum needed to reasonably make it through the next room.
Oh, geez. This mechanic? Yeah, this is gonna be tough.
Cape helps a bit with this multi-coin block as long as you jump carefully.

I'm guessing the way that gimmick works is that as soon as your coins hit zero, it instantly shrinks you, and then immediately acts as if you got hit by a normal hazard. But, it couldn't deliver that fatal hit while I was in the pipe.

Yep, you're being chased by a wall of lava in an autoscrolling area, and your money is draining again! And because it's autoscrolling, you can't really make up for a terrible starting coin total by racing faster!
So, should I go for the normal exit first, or the secret exit first? Vote now, and we'll find out which order I do this level's exits next time!
Ah, and on top of ensuring you won't be too short-changed, the lava wall is gone now! This gives you much more room to maneuver!
To be continued...
D'oh. Meant to fry that guy.
Hello, and welcome back to Bowser Rampages Again! Last time, I opened up the portal to Bowser's REAL hideout! So, let's see where this warp star takes me...
Aw, nuts. I needed to take the lower route for that Yoshi coin. Wait, maybe I can still get it from behind...
However, I don't think the P-switch will do much good in this area, but whatever.
Outta my way, Chucks! I'm in a hurry here!

Oh, and since your coins continue counting down while you're powering up or shrinking, taking a hit makes your coin situation worse, and grabbing a reserve power up hurts your coins even more! Honestly, this gimmick should've frozen your coin counter during any transformation animations.
Skip it, I don't need it now, and trying to collect it would just waste valuable time.
Those few coins in particular are almost impossible to claim without getting hurt, even if you do have a cape!
Really, Chuck! This is not the time to play Baseball!
Anyway, I've got the blue P-switch now, and I could take another feather, but... nah. I'll hang onto my flower.

These gray platforms are a bit cheap, because most of them start off already partially overlapping the munchers and you'll get bitten immediately if you land on those parts of them. (They really should've been placed better.)
Honestly, I think the lower coins here are much trickier to grab than the Yoshi coin up there.
Okay, see my coin total? It continuously counts down here, and if it ever hits zero... Death! Race forward and keep collecting coins to stay alive!
Okay, I think I'm close enough. Push!

I knew what to do there, and I still feel like I barely pulled it off. Also, imagine doing these gray platform jumps as small Mario with the lava wall present. I think that's nearly impossible unless you know exactly what to do, especially with how they partially overlap the munchers to begin with.
Alright, so next time, I'll be taking on Ninth Cave! And, it's a red level, so you know what that means! You guys get to vote!

Well, while that was a "science", I'm not going to do any rewinding since I didn't die, and instead I'll just revisit #5 Castle Depths to quickly replace my cape. (It's the nearest decent level for me to quickly get a cape in.)
Oh. God. No. NO! It's those horrible homing Bullet Bills! I really hate these things, because they're ridiculously fast, jerkish, and generally won't stop hounding you until you kill them!
Definitely check this pipe, since it takes you to midpoint!
Whew! I somehow made it without getting hurt there, mainly thanks to my cape! Some of those jumps are borderline impossible to make without getting hurt if you aren't caped.
Very tricky jumps here, and if you're trying to get every single coin, they're even trickier!
And now for a mostly sped up bonus game!
Hmm... Now, can I get a decent star total from the goal here?
Zwee! Halfway done with this place already.
And now this level is clear. However, I'm not entirely done with it yet. I'll want to reenter it just to show something off.
Yes, I'll take the flower this time!
I think it's odd like that in a way, because Lakitus will toss out silver coins instead of new spinies while a silver P-switch is active. Maybe the Lakitus were specially coded to do that...
Ooh, multi-coin block. Yes, you definitely want to clean this one out! Also, be sure to climb up the vine and collect the dozen coins up there!
Also, I get a cape here as a reward for hitting the Green Switch Palace waaay earlier in the game. Isn't that nice?
Try to keep this one cannon from firing!
Yeah, there's a lot of tricky jumps here, and you're not given much time to prepare for them.

I'd switch power ups for certain parts here, but the coin draining effect continues during the power up transformation animation, which I think is a little unfair. (It also continues through your shrinking animation if you get hit, which can make a bad situation worse!)
Fireballs may just be handy here.
BGM: Touhou 10.5 - The Ground's Color is Yellow

Once you get above 10 coins, that sound effect of your coins draining will stop as long as you stay above 10 coins. If you start hearing that sound again, that means you've dropped to 10 or fewer coins, and you should hurry up!
Oh, man. Bullet Bro. At least he doesn't use those jerkish homing bullets!
Better switch to my cape now.
Cool. I'm glad that Yoshi coin left me that option.
However, the game does throw you a small bone if you blow it here, and I'll make sure to show off why, even if I don't die.
Well, too bad, Bowser. I'm gonna get so close you wouldn't believe!
Hmm... I think the silver P-switch will work on the undead koopas, but I don't want to activate it yet...
Up next is Fiery Coin Rush! It's got an exclamation point at the end of its name, so that means I'm gonna have to hustle here!
And, if you don't have a cape and the lava wall is present, these last couple jumps are doozies!
Now, let's start exploring A Dark World...
This "1" platform probably should've been a "4", since even with the cape, safely grabbing all of the coins where this Banzai Bill appears is incredibly tricky.
I'm glad this bullet generator uses the regular Bullet Bills!
The cape is definitely useful here, even though I won't get coins from defeated enemies. (I wonder if the cape's general usefulness outweighs the flower's money-earning usefulness here...)
Hmm... I'm going to try doing "science" here. What happens if I enter the pipe just before my coins hit zero?
Okay, so we have an autoscrolling area here, and already, it's presenting me with some tricky jumps!
